{% extends "base-en.twig" %}

{% block main %}
<div class="intro">
    <h1>Euro Trucks Simulator 2</h1>
    <h2>The story of the game</h2>
    <p>Euro Truck Simulator 2 (ETS2) is a truck driving simulation game developed by SCS Software, released in 2012.</p>
    <p>
        In this game, you play as a truck driver who travels across Europe to deliver various goods. You start as a simple
        employee carrying out missions for different companies, then you earn money to buy your own truck and create your
        own transport company.
    </p>
    <h2>Game purpose and discovery</h2>
    <p>
        The gameplay consists of accepting delivery contracts, driving your truck over long distances through recreated
        European cities and countries (United Kingdom, France, Germany, Italy, Poland, etc.), while respecting traffic
        laws, managing your fuel and fatigue. You must deliver the cargo on time and in good condition to maximize your
        earnings. <span class="saut"></span>
        As you progress, you can expand your business by buying more trucks, hiring drivers, customizing your vehicles and
        unlocking new skills. The map is regularly expanded with DLCs adding new countries. <span class="saut"></span>
        The game is appreciated for its realism (driving physics, dynamic weather, traffic), its relaxing and meditative
        aspect, and its active community that creates mods. It has become a cult success, particularly popular with
        streamers and players looking for an authentic simulation experience rather than an action game.
    </p>
    <h2>Educational aspects</h2>

    <h3>European geography</h3>
    <p>
        ETS2 allows you to discover Europe interactively by traveling through faithfully recreated cities and regions.
        Players learn to locate countries, their capitals and the major roads that connect them, while admiring emblematic
        monuments and characteristic landscapes of each region.
    </p>
    <p>
        This virtual exploration develops a better understanding of real distances between European cities and the
        geographic specificities of the continent. It's a fun way to enrich your general knowledge about Europe.
    </p>

    <h3>Traffic laws</h3>
    <p>
        The game requires compliance with speed limits, traffic lights, priorities and traffic rules specific to each
        country. Violations are sanctioned by fines that reduce your earnings, encouraging safe and responsible driving.
    </p>
    <p>
        This realistic approach makes players aware of the importance of road safety and allows them to familiarize
        themselves with the differences in traffic laws between European countries. It's excellent learning for future
        drivers.
    </p>

    <h3>Career discovery</h3>
    <p>
        ETS2 offers an authentic immersion into the daily life of a truck driver: managing driving time, meeting delivery
        deadlines, planning routes and maintaining your vehicle. The game also simulates business management with hiring
        drivers and buying new trucks.
    </p>
    <p>
        This simulation allows you to understand the challenges and responsibilities of road transport, a sector essential
        to the European economy. Players develop logistics skills and discover a profession often overlooked but
        indispensable. Some ETS2 players have switched careers to become truck drivers after playing the game.
    </p>

</div>
{% endblock main %}

